<br>
We are implementing a new raid system in GoA and are extending it to our allies!  <br>
<br>
The new system allows us to hold raids once every Saturday! Over the past two years we have had the best attendance at raids planned far in advance, and on <br>
SATURDAYS AT 1PM EST. <br>
(10AM PST, 11AM MST, 12PM LST, 1pm EST, 6PM GMT)<br>
<br>
This will be the set time for our new LORE raids! Epic, quest, pickup, and loot raids are still planned and run separately. This is just an attempt to give you more raid experiences, and more steady scheduling.  Its taken months of work but we are ready to unveil it! We sincerely hope you enjoy this new twist in all of our storylines, raiding, and fun! <br>
<br>
As with all developments there will be bumps in the road, and we are starting small, but we hope for a smooth transition into this, the answer to your raiding needs we could never before offer! The best way to help make this work and keep this option open to you is to attend these raids. <br>
<br>
&lt;notification letter&gt;<br>
From GoA:<br>
Each raid lore volumn will tie game lore for three zones or mob races into our guild lore, and the reasons we are fighting them.   This Lore eventually will include and tie us in with all our Norrathian Alliance Allies that chose to participate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
There is a new page posted on the GoA website entitled &quot;RAIDS NOW IN PROGRESS&quot;. This page will house the past lore of raids as we go, and the new lore for the coming month. The basic concept is that we rotate a raid on each of these three targets for each saturday per month until we have completed the raid lore demand (basically once per target and once more at whatever one had the best turnout). <br>
<br>
The next month's lore is then posted with three new targets and we repeat the process. Once lore is built up for many zones, we can always have repeated lore that references back to our original reason for going to said dungeon or zone, if we want to go back. This will allow us to eventually both tie our guild lore in with every NAK Guild, always have interesting lore to go along with our raids, raid every saturday barring holidays, and REALLY HAVE FUN! <br>
There are endless benifits to this system, but the only ones who can make it work are you!~<br>
<br>
The first lore installment will be long, as it is the introduction to Lore Raids. Each subsequent entry or &quot;scroll&quot; will be shorter and shorter, as it will build off the previous ones. Be sure to read this Lore installments so you can follow later ones, even though lengthy. You can always find them posted at the page . If you have never read our brief GUILD LORE page at our site much of this will not make sense to you, stop by and catch up.<br>
Enjoy!<br>
<br>
Lore Entry #1: A Secret Enemy<br>
(found on webpage)<br>
<br>
We have posted dates for these on the calendar (whose link can be found on the &quot;raids in progress&quot; page and on this website), starting off after the USA's Thanksgiving, going on 2 raids before X-mas breaks, and then two more from that lore in January after the new years partying! The second Lore should be rolling for mid to late January! PLEASE KEEP UP TO DATE ON THE ALLIANCE CALENDAR AS THESE DATES WILL NOT BE EMAILED TO YOU OR POSTED HERE! Thanks all!<br>
Sincerely,<br>
Your Guild Administration and Officers<br>
&lt;end notification letter&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
